  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Forest Side Twin Rooms </strong>are around 23m² and sleep two people, with views of the forest. These rooms are available for sole use on request - please call to book.</p>
<p><strong>Jungfrau View Twin Rooms </strong>are around 21m²  and sleep two people. They have a balcony and are south, south west, or south east facing, with Jungfrau views. These rooms are available for sole use on request - please call to book.</p>
<p><strong>Jungfrau View Junior Suites </strong>are more spacious at around 32m² and sleep two people. They have a balcony and are south, south west, or south east facing, with Jungfrau views. Some junior suites have a walk-in shower in addition to the bath - these rooms must be confirmed in advance so please call us to book.</p>
<p><strong>Forest Side Family Rooms </strong>are around 28m² and sleep three to four (extra beds are one single sofa bed and one extra single bed). They have a lounge area and forest view.</p>
<p><strong>Jungfrau View Family Rooms</strong> are around 32m² and sleep three to four (extra beds are single beds). These rooms have a balcony and are south, south west, or south east facing, with Jungfrau views.</p>
<p>Family rooms are suitable for two adults and two children, or three adults.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Minibar</li>
<li>Bath with showerhead</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>General i</strong><strong>nformation</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Check-in time: <strong>3pm</strong></li>
<li>Check-out time: <strong>11am</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>A resort tourist tax of approx. CHF 4.30 per person per night is payable locally (children aged 6-15 years pay a reduced rate of CHF 1.80 per person per night, and guests aged 5 and under are exempt).</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>]]></roomsDescription>
